ryGenius — Lint fixes (PR #35, merged)**\n- Fixed 1 lint error and 6 lint warnings across pipeline and routes code\n- `let` → `const` for never-reassigned `itemsCreated` in normalizer.ts\n- Prefixed unused params `storeId`, `zipCode` with `_` in safeway.ts\n- Removed dead `parsePrice` function from wholefoodsmarket.ts\n- Removed unused `sql` import from pipeline/index.ts\n- Removed unused `error` bindings in catch blocks in routes.ts\n- Lint: 1 error + 13 warnings → 0 errors + 7 warnings (remaining are shadcn/ui fast-refresh, expected)\n\n**2. runeval — Next.js security upgrade (PR #30)**\n- Upgraded Next.js from 15.1.0 to 16.2.0 (major version bump)\n- Fixes 2 moderate vulnerabilities: unbounded disk cache growth (GHSA-3x4c-7xq6-9pq8), HTTP request smuggling (GHSA-ggv3-7p47-pfv8)\n- 0 vulnerabilities remaining. Build verified.\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: 5 low vulnerabilities remaining (transitive @google-cloud/storage deps). Open PR #23 for zip-slip security still pending review.\n- **waymo-sim**: `test_env.py` can't run due to missing `gymnasium` dependency (not in requirements.txt). Pre-existing issue.\n- **runCoach**: Empty repo — only README and LICENSE.\n- **assortedLLMTasks**: 11 uncommitted files on `claude/error-handling` branch — intentional from prior CLI session work on job pipeline.\n- **scripts**: No package.json, no centralized build/test. Extension folder uses MV2 (could migrate to MV3).\n- **llm-context**: Clean, well-maintained. No issues found.\n- **youtubeSpeedSetAndRemember**: On `claude/test-matrix` branch (1 commit ahead of main with TEST_MATRIX.md). Clean, no code issues. Stale branch could be merged or closed.\n- **groceryGenius**: 0 lint errors, 8 moderate esbuild vulns remaining (dev-only via drizzle-kit, not fixable without breaking change).\n- **runeval**: No tests. Major opportunity for future session.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-18 — Run 6\n\n### What was done\n\n**runeval — First test suite with 53 tests (PR #31, merged)**\n- Installed Vitest and configured it with `@/` path alias support\n- Added `npm test` and `npm run test:watch` scripts to package.json\n- Created 4 test files covering the most critical pure-function logic:\n  - `lib/__tests__/format.test.ts` (14 tests): formatDuration, formatPace, formatDistance — edge cases for zero, NaN, hours, padding\n  - `lib/__tests__/evaluateRun.test.ts` (26 tests): zone-based and intensity-based classification, pacing stability scoring, HR drift detection, form efficiency scoring, dynamics findings (cadence, GCT, vertical ratio), workout suggestions per classification, report structure validation\n  - `lib/__tests__/rateLimit.test.ts` (6 tests): request counting, key isolation, window expiry with fake timers, blocking at limit\n  - `lib/garmin/__tests__/health-processors.test.ts` (7 tests): webhook type detection for various payload shapes, ALL_WEBHOOK_KEYS exports\n- All 53 tests pass, build verified\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **runeval**: Has 53 tests now. Future opportunities: test conversation parsers (chatgpt/claude/gemini), test health metric normalization, add API route integration tests.\n- **assortedLLMTasks**: 11 uncommitted files on `claude/error-handling` branch — intentional from prior CLI session.\n- **scripts**: Extension folder already MV3 — no migration needed.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-19 — Run 7\n\n### What was done\n\n**promptlibrary — JSON parsing safety for all API write endpoints (PR #14)**\n- Added `.catch(() => null)` + explicit 400 response to 7 unprotected `req.json()` calls\n- Affected routes: POST /api/prompts, PATCH /api/prompts/[id], POST /api/prompts/[id]/outputs, POST /api/prompts/[id]/ratings, POST /api/prompts/[id]/versions, POST /api/moderation, PATCH /api/moderation\n- Previously malformed JSON would crash handlers with unhandled exceptions (500 errors)\n- Now returns clear `{\"error\": \"Invalid or missing JSON body\"}` with 400 status\n- Matches pattern already used