or build)\n\n**2. promptlibrary — First test suite with 66 tests (PR #15/#16/#17, auto-merged)**\n- Installed Vitest and configured with `@/` path alias support\n- Added `npm test` and `npm run test:watch` scripts\n- Created 4 test files covering all pure-function library modules:\n  - `validation.test.ts` (30 tests): title, body, output, tags, rating, URL, platform validation with boundary cases\n  - `sanitize.test.ts` (19 tests): XSS prevention, allowed/disallowed HTML tags, PII detection for emails, API keys, AWS keys, credit cards, SSNs, phones, bearer tokens\n  - `apiKey.test.ts` (7 tests): key format, length, hex-only chars, uniqueness, hash determinism\n  - `db.test.ts` (4 tests): simpleHash consistency, whitespace trimming, uniqueness\n- All 66 tests pass, build verified\n- Deployed to staging — API healthy, page SSR 500 is pre-existing (production works fine)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **promptlibrary staging**: SSR rendering returns 500 but API health is fine — likely missing env vars or DB state after hard reset. Not caused by test changes.\n- **promptlibrary**: Future test opportunities — integration tests for API routes (POST /api/prompts, search, moderation), rate limiting module\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-19 — Run 10\n\n### What was done\n\n**groceryGenius — 72 new unit tests for core modules (PR #44, merged)**\n- Added 3 test files covering all testable pure-function modules:\n  - `validator.test.ts` (36 tests): `validateProduct` name/price/HTML sanitization, image URL validation, numeric field edge cases, boolean defaults, sourceProductId; `validateProducts` batch filtering and rejection counting\n  - `normalizer.test.ts` (26 tests): `normalizeUnit` weight conversions (lb/oz/kg/g), volume conversions (gal/qt/pt/fl oz/l/ml), count units (each/ea/ct/pack/bunch), quantity division, case insensitivity, whitespace trimming, edge cases\n  - `auth.test.ts` (10 tests): `hashPassword` format and salt randomness; `verifyPassword` correct/wrong passwords, malformed hashes, special characters, unicode\n- Test suite now at 81 tests total (was 9)\n- All tests pass, build verified\n- Deployed to staging — 200 OK\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **groceryGenius**: 81 tests now. Future opportunities: integration tests for API routes, React component tests (would need jsdom/happy-dom)\n- **runeval**: Local repo was on `claude/auto-test-suite` branch (stale). Has 5 stale local branches to clean up.\n- **waymo-sim**: Local repo on `claude/auto-engine-bugfixes` branch (stale). Has 2 stale local branches.\n- **groceryGenius**: 7 stale local branches could be cleaned up\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-19 — Run 11\n\n### What was done\n\n**runeval — Restore ESLint after Next.js 16 broke `next lint` (PR #35, merged)**\n- Next.js 16 removed the built-in `next lint` command, leaving `npm run lint` completely broken\n- Added standalone ESLint flat config (`eslint.config.mjs`) with:\n  - TypeScript support via `typescript-eslint`\n  - React hooks plugin (`eslint-plugin-react-hooks`)\n  - Next.js plugin (`@next/eslint-plugin-next`)\n  - Node.js globals for server-side files\n  - Scripts and prisma directories excluded\n- Fixed 7 lint errors surfaced by the new config:\n  - `app/api/imports/upload/route.ts`: `let data` → `const data` (removed dead ZIP try/catch)\n  - `lib/garmin/adapter.ts`: attached `{ cause: err }` to 2 re-thrown errors\n  - `lib/logger.ts`: replaced dynamic `require(\"fs\")` / `require(\"child_process\")` with static ESM imports\n- Updated `npm run lint` script: `next lint` → `eslint .`\n- Result: 0 errors, 96 warnings (all pre-existing `no-explicit-any` or `no-unused-vars`)\n- Cleaned up 5 stale local branches\n- Deployed to staging — 401 (auth required, app running correctly)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **runeval**: Lint now works. 96 warnings remain — mostly `no-explicit-any` in admin API routes. Good candidate for gradual type improvement.\n- **runeval remote**: Points to archiv