iewDetailPage (reviewer attribution), HomePage (trusted people cards), PeoplePage (reviewer cards)\n- ReviewCard: image thumbnail (h-40, rounded-xl, object-cover) displayed above body text when `review.imageUrl` is set\n- ReviewDetailPage: already had image rendering for `review.imageUrl` (from Tier 1 build) — now has reviewer avatar too\n- Seed data: 5 of 10 reviewers have Unsplash avatar URLs (Maya, Jordan, Sam, Lina, Priya); 5 remaining use initial-letter fallback\n- Seed data: 6 of 38 reviews have image URLs (ramen, pad see ew, croissants, Lisbon, Tokyo, espresso machine)\n- Seed insert updated to pass `imageUrl` from review data instead of always null\n- 11 new tests: schema validation (accept/reject URL, omit imageUrl, omit avatarUrl), API storage (POST stores imageUrl/avatarUrl, defaults to null), GET returns image fields\n- 92 total tests (was 81), all passing, TypeScript clean, build verified\n- Playwright visual verification: homepage (avatar photos + review thumbnails), people page (photo avatars + letter fallbacks), person page (large avatar + review images), review detail (full image + reviewer avatar), mobile layout\n- Stale branch cleanup: pruned 1 remote branch (claude/fix-recover-image-support)\n\n**All Tier 2 features now complete:** trust badges (#5), review reactions (#6), responsive mobile (#7), image support (#8).\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: All Tier 1 and Tier 2 features complete. Next work would be Tier 3: category landing pages (#9), reviewer comparison (#10), feed page (#11), share links (#12), sort & pagination (#13)\n- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 33\n\n### What was done\n\n**trustedCircle — Category landing pages (Tier 3 #9, first Tier 3 feature) (PRs #33-#34, auto-merged)**\n- New `GET /api/categories/:slug/insights` endpoint returning:\n  - Category stats: total reviews, total reviewers, average rating\n  - Top reviewers (up to 5) ranked by review count in category, with per-category avg rating and trust badges\n  - Most helpful reviews sorted by reaction count (only reviews with reactions)\n  - Trending items: aggregated by item name (case-insensitive), showing count, avg rating, and link to latest review\n- Enhanced CategoryPage from flat review list to rich landing page with 4 sections:\n  - Stats header with review/reviewer counts and avg rating\n  - Top reviewers section with avatar cards, review counts, and trust badges\n  - Trending items section with clickable pill buttons linking to reviews\n  - Most helpful reviews section (only shown when reviews have reactions)\n  - All reviews grid (existing, now labeled)\n- 7 new tests: full insights response shape, 404, empty category, reaction filtering, reviewer ordering, 5-reviewer limit, item name aggregation\n- 99 total tests (was 92), all passing, TypeScript clean, build verified\n- API verified via curl: food (6 reviews, 3 reviewers, 4.3 avg), tech (4 reviews, 1 reviewer, 4.4 avg)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: Category landing pages done (Tier 3 #9). Remaining Tier 3: reviewer comparison (#10), feed page (#11), share links (#12), sort & pagination (#13)\n- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 34\n\n### What was done\n\n**trustedCircle — Reviewer comparison (Tier 3 #10) (PR #35, auto-merged)**\n- New `GET /api/compare?handles=handle1,handle2` endpoint returning:\n  - Both reviewers' full data with categories, badges, and all reviews\n  - Shared categories (by ID intersection)\n  - Shared items: items both reviewers have reviewed (case-insensitive name matching), with each reviewer's reviews grouped\n- New ComparePage with:\n  - Reviewer selection dropdowns (with avatar previews, excludes already-selected reviewer)\n  - Side-by-side profile cards with stats (review count, avg rating)\n  - \"Items Both Reviewed\" section showing side-by-side reviews of the same items\n  - Shared category filter pills\n  - Side-by-side review grids (filterable by category)\n- \"Compare\" nav link added to header with ArrowLeftRight icon\n- 8 new tests: input validation (400 for bad params, 404 for missing reviewer), full comparison response shape, shared category detection, shared item matching (case-insensitive), empty overlap handling\n- 107 total tests (was 99), all passing, TypeScript clean, build verified\n- API verified via curl: compare endpoint returns correct reviewer data and shared categories\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: Reviewer comparison done (Tier 3 #10). Remaining Tier 3: feed page (#11), share links (#12), sort & pagination (#13)\n- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 35\n\n### What was done\n\n**trustedCircle — Social timeline feed page (Tier 3 #11) (PR #36, auto-merged)**\n- New `GET /api/feed` endpoint with:\n  - Cursor-based pagination (20 per page)\n  - Category filter via `?category=slug`\n  - Bulk reaction counts (helpful/agree) per review — no N+1 queries\n  - User's own reaction state per review\n  - Suggested reviewers (non-followed, with categories and review counts) for discovery\n- Rewrote CirclePage from flat list into social timeline:\n  - Day separators (\"Today\", \"Yesterday\", weekday names, full dates)\n  - Relative timestamps (\"2h ago\", \"3d ago\") on each card\n  - FeedCard component with reviewer avatar header, category badge, inline reactions using pre-fetched data\n  - Category filter pills (horizontal scroll)\n  - \"Load more\" cursor pagination button\n  - SuggestedReviewerCard for empty/small circles\n  - Two empty states: no follows (browse people CTA) and no reviews (suggested reviewers grid)\n  - \"People you might like\" section below feed when circle is small\n- 7 new tests: empty feed, suggested reviewers, reaction data in feed, user reaction state, category filtering, cursor pagination, suggestion exclusion of followed reviewers\n- 114 total tests (was 107), all passing, TypeScript clean, build verified\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: Feed page done (Tier 3 #11). Remaining Tier 3: share links (#12), sort & pagination (#13)\n- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 36\n\n### What was done\n\n**trustedCircle — Sort & pagination (Tier 3 #13) (PR #37-#39, auto-merged)**\n- Server-side sort support on 3 API endpoints:\n  - `GET /api/reviewers?sort=name|reviews|newest` — sort people by name (default), review count, or newest\n  - `GET /api/categories/:slug/reviews?sort=newest|rating_high|rating_low&page=N` — sort + offset pagination (20/page)\n  - `GET /api/reviewers/:handle?sort=newest|rating_high|rating_low` — sort reviewer's reviews\n- Reusable `SortPills` component for pill-style sort UI (ink/sand active state)\n- PeoplePage: sort pills (Name A–Z, Most reviews, Newest) alongside search filter\n- CategoryPage: sort pills in \"All reviews\" section + prev/next page navigation\n- PersonPage: sort pills below category filter for review ordering\n- 10 new tests: 3 for reviewer sort, 4 for category review sort + pagination, 3 for reviewer profile sort\n- 124 total tests (was 114), all passing, TypeScript clean, build verified\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: Sort & pagination done (Tier 3 #13). Remaining Tier 3: share links (#12)\n- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 37","numLines":200,"startLine":700,"totalLines":1234}}}
